sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1972014
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: dszBBAC with tac promoter and dszD with lac promotor induced by IPTG
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Each single biodesulfurization enzyme gene was synthesized by Generay and we constructed them together and suquencing comformed. the sequences can be found in NCBI (GenBank Accession number L37363.1) The T7 RNA polymerase controled system is PCRed from E.coli Bl21.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
We constructed dszBCAD genes with T7 promoter and IPTG controled system and choose E.coli as our host cell.T7 RNA polymerase will not be expressed without IPTG. When IPTG is added to 1 mM, T7 RNA polymerase will be expressed and dszBCAD genes with T7 promoter will be greatly expressed by the host cell. The four enzymes will be successful expressed and these four enzymes convert dibenzothiophene (DBT) undergoes through three successive oxidation steps and one a hydrolytic step to 2-hydroxybiphenyl (2HBP) by the 4s pathway.
Each single biodesulfurization enzyme gene was synthesized by Generay and we constructed them together and suquencing comformed. the sequences can be found in NCBI (GenBank Accession number L37363.1)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Shuli Liang

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1972005
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This single monooxygenase gene was synthesized whith E.coli codon optimized by Generay and the sequence was found in NCBI (GenBank Accession number L37363.1)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
DszB is a a desulfinase which can convert 2-(2-hydroxybiphenyl) sulfinate (HBPS) to 2-hydroxybiphenyl (2HBP) during the 4S pathway, in which dibenzothiophene (DBT) undergoes three successive oxidation steps and one a hydrolytic step leading to the formation of 2-hydroxybiphenyl (2HBP)
This single monooxygenase gene was synthesized whith E.coli codon optimized by Generay and the sequence was found in NCBI (GenBank Accession number L37363.1)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Shuli Liang

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg
